  "texts": [
    "Covariance: statistical tool used to understand the relationship between two variables.",
    "A positive covariance means both variables increase together, while a negative covariance suggests that they move in opposite directions (Koch et al., 1982).",
    "DAPI (4,6-diamidino-2phenylindole): fluorescent probe that binds to the minor groove (A-T rich) of double-stranded DNA (Kapuscinski, 1995).",
    "Diffusion weighted image (DWI): MRI technique that measures water diffusion in tissues.",
    "DWI images are used to diagnose and monitor a variety of neurological disorders (Baliyan et al., 2016)."
  ],
